    },
    {
      "text": "World Games is a sports video game developed by Epyx for the Commodore 64 in 1986. Versions for the Apple IIGS, Amstrad CPC, ZX Spectrum, Master System and other contemporary systems were also released. The NES version was released by Milton Bradley, and ported by Software Creations on behalf of producer Rare. The Master System version was done by Sega.\nThe game is a continuation of the Epyx sports line that includes Summer Games and Winter Games.\nWorld Games was made available in Europe for the Wii Virtual Console on April 25, 2008.",
      "lang": "en",
      "source": "wikipedia_en"
